description: At last we return to the story of Chuckles, who was last seen in the custody of none other than Cobra Commander! But is he a prisoner... or an honored guest? Can the man whose life was ruined by pretending to join Cobra have finally given in?
name: Sidewinder

description:
What if you could open a doorway into another world? When a strange, feral young woman suddenly appears in the middle of the highway causing a massive explosion, Dr. Tom Mason doesn’t quite know what to make of her, or the strange device on her arm…

Acclaimed fantasy novelist George R.R. Martin  scripts this all-new comic-book adventure!

Now that all the weirdness has been explained, Angel and company are looking to get back to what they do best. Except an old enemy with the letters W and H comes back, Angel gets transported, and a whole new can of demony worms is opened. Literally.
name: The Wolf, the Ram, and the Heart, Part 1

description: Eisner Award-winning horror masters Mike Mignola and Richard Corben present this bloodcurdling double-feature comic with Hellboy entering two very different, but very deadly, houses--a carnivorous home and a pagan temple, both hungry for human sacrifices.
name: Sullivan's Reward; The House of Sebek

description: Leon's plans for the show take a turn for the worse when Valerie returns to Los Angeles.
name: Born to Lose, Live to Whatever

volume.name: Whatever Happened to Baron Von Shock?

description: Stunning, never-before-seen artwork by series artist VICTOR SANTOS. From sketches and layouts to character designs and fully painted pin-ups, a showcase to inspire every fan of the Templar mythos. Featuring an ALL-NEW Mice Templar short story that links Volume 2 to next month's debut of Volume 3. Nominated for six Harvey Awards!
Hip Flask versus agents of MAPPO –- and Flask has nothing left to lose.
name: Death Roll!

description: The end is finally here. The elder’s plan is revealed! Zechariah's final fate is decided! Wolf-Man’s astounding adventure is coming to a close. Every moment from the beginning of the series to now has been leading to this. Don’t miss this special oversized series-ending extravaganza!
name: Legacy, Conclusion

description: The best-selling WORLD OF WARCRAFT comic series returns in time for a worldwide CATACLYSM! A series of grisly, animalistic murders have rocked the walled town of Gilneas. A famous detective sets out to discover the perpetrators and finds far more than he bargained for. To find the truth, he must delve through years of twisted history – both the history of his family and Gilneas itself. This pivotal 5-issue miniseries explores the in-depth lore of the Worgen!
name: #1 (of 5)

volume.name: World of Warcraft: Curse of the Worgen

description: Features the first appearance of Dark Angel.

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
The Deadly Game

They were twins and well named, were the Hawk Brothers... David and Jonas, fighter pilots, U.S.A.F., two men apparently indifferent to the great principles involved, fighting their own private war, trying to score the most victories... grown boys riding the skies on lightning wing with awesome powers to destroy... powers they used with skill and frequency!

The Crazy Kid

No Description

Old Woman's Fancy (Text Only Story)

The Intruders

The flight of three bombers over the critical polar region was detected by the dew line radar stations in the North American polar regions and the information was transmitted to the air defense command! Flight plans of our own planes were checked-- none were in that area! So... out long range interceptors scrambled!

The Hurricane Fighters

No Description

The Unimportant Hero

He was young, not college trained... only a corporal and he felt like a very small and unessential cog in the giant Air Force machinery! Yet, he loved to fly... he loved big XB-585 that were so awkward on the ground, of such graceful beauty in the air! Air Force corporal Bud Candless didn't want to get out but he had excellent reasons for the decision he hated to make...

A Taste of Fear

Flying a Martin Marauder is bad enough... every time I poured on the power and felt the huge engines rocket down the bumpy North African runaway, I got petrified... landing the stubby-winged medium bomber was even worse! Just flying the B-26 was enough to make an old man out of me even though I was only twenty-three back in 1943 when we were fighting in North Africa! But, to make it worse, I had to have a Tennessee Wildcat for a top turret gunner... who thought I was yellow! He didn't know what fear was... and hated anyone who did!

3 Minutes

This unidentified plane is cruising at 780 MPH, coming South over our Canadian border... it could be the enemy... one of a thousand sent to destroy our cities! If it is... are we ready? Can we avert the disaster that might be on the way? It will be over one of our cities in just... 3 Minutes

Simply Scouts (Text Only Story)

The Hidden Enemy

Despite the most elaborate security precautions at the huge air base, there were saboteurs at work... but who? Was it one of the civilian technicians who worked closely with the Air Force on th ultra-modern techniques and equipment being developed? Or a man wearing the U.S. Air Force uniform who was trying to send airmen to their deaths! Whoever it was did a nasty job on the B-58 Hustler!

Bombing Mission

We were in the Aleutian Islands... and we had to find a Japanese strongpoint on Kiska, the only island still in enemy hands in May, 1942! I was navigator aboard the B-25 Mitchell Toting a load of 500 lb. bombs and all I had to do was find the way back!

Ground Support Missions (One Page Story)

Low Destroyer

At first, when ordered to strafe specific ground targets, captain Art Rudolph had been wary of flying too low where the 88mm guns could fire point-blank at his P-51 Mustang and blast it to pieces! But he forced himself to go low - until in the end he almost overdid it!

The Gripper

S/Sgt Dinky Malone worked long hard hours keeping the B-25 Mitchell of captain Otto Haabst airworthy! Haabst flew more missions than any medium bomber pilot in the South Pacific... and Sgt. Malone swore he must be the lousiest pilot to judge by the amount of damage he came back with each time he returned! The line chief never got tired of spouting off on the subject!

The Elements of An Aircraft (Text Only Story)

Parmalee's Pack

There were four of them... Devore, Reynolds, Mizzed, and Gajanian... four fighter pilots taught to fly by Captain "Tiger" Tom Parmalee, checked out in the first jets in 1949, razzed, drilled, maligned, and molded into the kind of men the U.S. Air Force needed so badly when Korea became an ugly reality in 1950! Tiger Tom Parmalee lived just long enough to get them into action! He didn't come back from a mission one day... but to his pack of cats, Tiger Tom would never die! And in moments of great danger, when death snarled and clawed at these four special men... something not quite mortal reached out from limbo to help them stay alive!

How High How Fast (One Page Story)

In real life, Roto, Boromid and Ah-Dol are average kids with average problems, but in the virtual world of Lost Saga, they're heroes. They might even become legends...if they can stop bickering long enough to level up. Whether it's werewolves running rampant or a gorgeous pair of troublesome thieves, our boys must be ready for anything, because in Lost Saga nothing is what it seems and murder can happen with a click of a mouse.

----------

Roto, Boromid and Ah-dol are high school friends who are also a terrific team of online gamers. They come across the game LostSaga and discover a world unlike anything they have seen before! When Roto finds an ID card with "Yureka" printed on it, he hacks into the game using "Yureka" as his identity. The trouble is, Yureka already has a identity all her own...
name: Vol. 1

description: Roto tries to return to the virtual world of Lost Saga, but he discovers that his card has expired and he can't log on. When he comes across an ID card with the name "Yureka" on it, Roto has found a new way to get into the game. The problem is, you're not supposed to log on with someone else's card. But when you're a hero in the virtual world, sometimes the rules have to be broken! The action and adventure are taken to a whole new level, until the moment when Roto meets up with the real Yureka...
name: Vol. 2

description: Is Yureka a real character or is she a replacement of the real one? As Roto and Yureka head out to enter a tournament, Roto is getting close to revealing the truth about his mysterious companion Yureka...
name: Vol. 3

description: A mysterious person joins Team Aradon just as they begin their battle against Baltisse's team. Aradon single handedly defeats Baltisse, while the powers of Alpha, Team Ardon's myster member, are yet to be revealed...however, he bears a striking similarity to Ah-Dol. Meanwhile, Team Roto and Yureka battle Team Rapha and John. Looks like Yureka and Roto have the upper hand as they both possess amazing power and strength, but who will ultimately win the battle? In this exciting volume, three battles are fought with nothing less than pure action in the arena.
name: Vol. 4

description: In a revealing flashback, King Lucifen reminisces about the shaky beginnings of Lost Saga and the late Dr. J, a mysterious and talented programmer who overcame much adversity to develop the framework for the game--which led to the creation of Yureka. But enough about the past! The end of the semifinal matches is upon our heroes, as John and Rapha continue their battle with Roto and Yureka. As the fight builds to a grueling climax, whose sacrifice will be great enough to win?
name: Vol. 5

description: Rapha is roaming around as a spirit, but is caught by the dark priest Il-ban. The semi-finals are over and the finals are between Team Yureka and Roto and Team Aradon and Alpha. Roto succeeds in identifying the mysterious Alpha. Roto feels like there's more to the competition than meets the eye, but he doesn't know what.
name: Vol. 6

description: Finally, the characters of Lost Saga are back in action, but this time in the real world! After finishing one of his most deadly assignments, Roto comes face-to-face with Alpha...and the true identity of all the players are revealed!
name: Vol. 7

description: The true identity of all the players has been revealed! The group follows their own path to only end up in a bigger game. But is everyone truly ready for the mysteries and challenges awaiting them in the Last Saga?
name: Vol. 8

description: The Monster King has the world caught in his clutches. His reign of terror seems to be merciless without weakness. Still, that does not cause Roto and Basara from balking at fighting this monstrosity. First, they must destroy the devilish Cube, one of the four "Devas," to continue their quest. Will they finish the game or will this be "Game Over"?
name: Vol. 9

description: Adol and Boromid are nearing defeat before Il-Ban decides to unleash the power of the Hella's Chris dagger. Il-Ban stabs Capri to give him enough power to take down the wicked Muriah. Now, they must face Neogia, one of the four Devas. Will this diabolical mind-riding spirit be too much for them?
name: Vol. 10

description: Roto, Aradon, Boromid, Adol, and Yureka face off against the Monster King, while the other users begin to question their motive for fighting on behalf of Luciferia. Roto discovers that the Monster King has a few tricks of his own stored up in the castle's basement. With Aradon and the others distracting the Monster King upstairs, Roto unfolds a mystery that may change the way the entire Lost Saga game is played--and it could mean game over!
name: Vol. 11

description: "A round steel door with thick chains draped around it. Pretty underwhelming, honestly," said Roto...but that was before he opened the door. As soon as it's unsealed, the door that supposedly led to the regenerator of Kast, unleashes a monster so powerful that even the Monster King himself is taken aback. Who could have planted such a thing in Lost Saga?
name: Vol. 12
